1.Highlights the changed section and so no need to go through the unnecessary data.
2.having the versions of program will help to revert any unnecessary changes made mistakenly.
3.Pros:- Can commit whenever we want withou maing unnecessary commmits.
  Cons:- If forgot to commit then will loose the changed data.
4.Saving multiple dependent files in one commit is better option as compare to commit each file seperaely.
5.git log :- displays all the commits made so far with the description,author name and time.
  git diff:- can see the changes done in the new version of data with the new commit.
6.Can go back at any time and look the changes made and can revert to the required state.
7. Using git, will open editor, have versios.